Open package of @chicken{} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; season with half the @fajita spice blend{1%tablespoon}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired. Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{}. Wash out pan.

While chicken cooks, drain and rinse @black beans{1%unit}.

In a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine beans, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, remaining fajita spice blend, @water{2%tbsp}, @butter{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and pepper. Cover tightly with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until beans are warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Mash about half the beans with a #potato masher{} or #fork{}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

> If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

Arrange @flour tortillas{6%unit}, chicken, beans, and @Mexican cheese blend{1%cup} family style for everyone to assemble their own quesadillas.

> Place filling of your choice on one half of a tortilla; fold tortilla in half over filling to form a quesadilla.

Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add quesadillas and cook on one side until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Carefully flip quesadillas; cook until golden brown and cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

> Work in batches if needed, adding another drizzle of oil between batches and reducing heat if quesadillas start to brown too quickly.

Halve quesadillas.

Serve quesadillas with @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, @guacamole{4%tablespoon}, and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} on the side. (Don't forget to serve with any extra items you may have ordered to build out your meal!)

> Shellfish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.